Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
In my hometown winter is kind of sad. When I was a small kid we used to have a lot of snow but now it has been replaced by clouds, wind, and rain, making it a colder version of fall. Winter is also really cold in my hometown but in a general basis you get used to it, so much so that you're not afraid of the cold anymore.